@nateoo0 This is understandable - because in the video, it is clear that no one cares, just like the knife murders we have seen across the country before.
But it is also surprising that the streets of Beijing are full of police, plainclothes, auxiliary police, assistant police, Chaoyang aunties, security guards, and the murderer just swaggered and left.
So it also exposes a question, what is the significance of Beijing's security measures, monitoring networks, and police deployment?
